cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR 

This paper deals with vision-based activity recognition, which is a core topic in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a hybrid model that involves sub-image histogram equalization enhancement and k-key pose human silhouettes, which suggests that it may belong to cs.MM (Multimedia). The use of machine learning techniques for recognition also indicates that it could be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the recognition of human activities, which is a common topic in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper also deals with security and surveillance applications, which could place it under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
